                                                                                                 NIST SP 800-160, VOL. 2, REV. 1                                         DEVELOPING CYBER-RESILIENT SYSTEMS
                                                                                                 _________________________________________________________________________________________________



                                                                                                  system of interest              A system whose life cycle is under consideration in the context
                                                                                                  [ISO 15288]                     of [ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288:2015].
                                                                                                  [SP 800-160 v1]                 Note: A system of interest can be viewed as the system that is the focus
                                                                                                                                  of the systems engineering effort. The system of interest contains
                                                                                                                                  system elements, system element interconnections, and the
                                                                                                                                  environment in which they are placed.
                                                                                                  system-of-systems               System of interest whose system elements are themselves
                                                                                                  [SP 800-160 v1]                 systems; typically, these entail large-scale interdisciplinary
                                                                                                  [INCOSE14]                      problems with multiple heterogeneous distributed systems.
                                                                                                                                  Note: In the system-of-systems environment, constituent systems may
This publication is available free of charge from: https://doi.org/10.6028/NIST.SP.800-160v2r1




                                                                                                                                  not have a single owner, may not be under a single authority, or may
                                                                                                                                  not operate within a single set of priorities.
                                                                                                  technical risk                  The risk associated with the evolution of the design and the
                                                                                                  [NASA19]                        production of the system of interest affecting the level of
                                                                                                                                  performance necessary to meet the stakeholder expectations
                                                                                                                                  and technical requirements.
                                                                                                                                  Note: Technical risk is often associated with novel technologies being
                                                                                                                                  proposed for integration into the system of interest or being used in
                                                                                                                                  systems that interact with the system of interest. It can also be
                                                                                                                                  associated with new discoveries of inherent vulnerabilities in
                                                                                                                                  technologies, or with products being withdrawn from use or losing
                                                                                                                                  support.
                                                                                                  technique                       See cyber resiliency technique.
                                                                                                  threat event                    An event or situation that has the potential for causing
                                                                                                  [SP 800-30]                     undesirable consequences or impact.
                                                                                                  threat scenario                 A set of discrete threat events, associated with a specific threat
                                                                                                  [SP 800-30]                     source or multiple threat sources, partially ordered in time.
                                                                                                  threat source                   Any circumstance or event with the potential to adversely
                                                                                                  [CNSSI 4009]                    impact organizational operations (including mission, functions,
                                                                                                                                  image, or reputation), organizational assets, individuals, other
                                                                                                                                  organizations, or the Nation through an information system via
                                                                                                                                  unauthorized access, destruction, disclosure, or modification of
                                                                                                                                  information, and/or denial of service.
                                                                                                  trustworthiness                 Worthy of being trusted to fulfill whatever critical requirements
                                                                                                  [SP 800-160 v1]                 may be needed for a particular component, subsystem, system,
                                                                                                                                  network, application, mission, business function, enterprise, or
                                                                                                                                  other entity.




